data.text:
Originally released in 1995, Brothas Doobie is the second album by the Los Angeles-based Latino rap group Funkdoobiest. The album contains all the original members Son Doobie (Jason Vasquez), DJ Ralph M (Ralph Medrano), and Tomahawk Funk (Tyrone Pacheco). The latter left group after this release.

The album contains the famous and controversial track "Superhoes", which also appeared in the soundtrack to the film Friday, starring NWA's Ice Cube. The executive producer of the album is Muggs (Cypress Hill). DJ Lethal (House Of pain, Limp Bizkit) produced the track "It Ain't Going Down".
